{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5763fd68-1008-4ba9-9456-fb6645bc9517","content":"The project is small (one file), but here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py` — line 3:**\n```\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is a classic untestable static. `datetime.now()` is called directly, making it impossible to control the time in tests.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `django.utils.timezone.now` and inject/mock it in tests, or use the [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) library:\n\n```python\n# Option 1: Use django.utils.timezone (preferred in Django)\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()  # timezone-aware + easily mockable\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\n```python\n# In tests, freeze time with:\nfrom freezegun import freeze_time\n\n@freeze_time(\"2026-01-01\")\ndef test_index(self):\n    ...\n```\n\n> **Note:** The `detect-static-dependencies` skill is designed for C# codebases, so I scanned manually. This project only has one file with one static call site.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dc4e9ebc-154e-483d-b139-317533f47fc5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The detect-static-dependencies skill is specifically for C# source files, so it won't work for Python. Let me do a manual scan. The project is very small - just one file. Let me grep for common Python untestable statics across the project.","outputTokens":354,"requestId":"A043:3B0D3D:1D08D13:211B702:69FEA1D9"},"id":"e6d0ba7c-d62b-48cc-a7b1-5a758a361ab1","timestamp":"2026-05-09T02:54:26.110Z","parentId":"97bdfd5e-e5a2-4491-af42-f1699805bf89"}
